# Project Overview

This project is a Yarn workspaces monorepo of React UI component libraries built with TypeScript and Material UI (MUI). Storybook is used for local development, documentation and testing of components.

The project consists of two main types of component libraries:

- **@eduriam-ui/core**
  - This is the core library of components built on Material UI components.
  - It contains components, interfaces, types and default theme settings.
  - All business logic of components is defined in this library.
- **theme libraries** (e.g. @eduriam-ui/[theme-name])
  - These libraries import the @eduriam-ui/core library
  - Their main purpose is to create a custom theme (styles) for the components
  - They can overwrite theme configurations and overwrite the styling of the individual components
  - They must follow the interfaces exported by the @eduriam-ui/core library
